reviewText: As a Montrealer, amateur musician and jazz lover, this film was a must for my collection. It's a history of a time when the city was wide open, and a history of the music that flourished in two languages. Like the music, the story is strong and passionate.
Good story of love that is sometime impossible to keep. I have read that Roy Dupuis did not play the piano, but it looks pretty real.
I loved the music and the story. It captures Jack Paradise's dysfunctional childhood and how that lead to his love of Jazz music yet his desire for a normal life.
